decision_conditions:
Condition : 15 - No development shall take place, including any works of demolition, until details of ecological mitigation, including bat roosting features, as set out in the approved Bat Survey Report ref. 4576_01_B dated 26 June 2020 shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning. 

The mitigation measures shall include:
"	Obtaining any relevant licences from Natural England (or registration with relevant licensing scheme) to allow proposed works, and therefore destruction of roost/disturbance of bats, to be undertaken;
"	A method statement  and commitment for works to be undertaken in accordance;
"	Supervised (by a CIEEM certified ecologist) removal of roosting features with any bats found during demolition safely transferred to alternative roosting locations such as bat boxes;
"	Provision of alternative roosting features for bats within the proposed scheme, including number and details of exact location, specification and design of the habitats. 
"	measures to prevent disturbance to roosts during construction, habitat enhancements, specifications for lighting, etc.


The mitigation measure shall be carried out and installed as approved prior to the first occupation of any dwelling hereby approve, and maintained as such thereafter.
